false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2021-04-28T13:56:50Z", "updated_at": "2021-07-21T07:09:59Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "For HTTP-based downloads ORA uses `download_url()`. However, this function unconditonally logs what it does at `INFO` level, flooding the screen with\r\n\r\n```\r\n[INFO] Downloading 'http://studyforrest.ds.inm7.de/d47/59300-5563-467d-be5f-e5b164fb3060/annex/objects/50/MG/MD5E-s37--c2fc4f1d5c1ae4db14689b90b1b08971.csv/MD5E-s37--c2fc4f1d5c1ae4db14689b90b1b08971.csv' into '.git/annex/tmp/MD5E-s37--c2fc4f1d5c1ae4db14689b90b1b08971.csv' \r\n```\r\n\r\nIMHO this is a largely pointless message, and it torpedos the whole idea of `fsck -q` which helps you spot problems -- that are now drowning in the noise.\r\n\r\nWe can either lower the log level, or stop using `download_url()`.\r\n\r\nSwitching to plain `requests` might give us an easier angle at enabling progress reporting via git-annex, but we also loose the authentication handling.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5610/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5610/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}